</div>
</p>

<p><em>WHEREAS veterans in their line of duty have shown extreme acts of bravery and courage;</em> <br>
<em>AND WHEREAS veterans have neglected needs when returning to civilian life,</em></p>

<p><em>NOW, THEREFORE, Her Majesty, by and with the advice and consent of the House of Commons of Canada, enacts as follows:</em></p>

<h3 id="short-title">Short Title</h3>



<h4 id="short-title-1">Short Title</h4>

<ol>
<li>This Act may be cited as the <em>Support for Veterans Act</em>.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="interpretation">Interpretation</h3>



<h4 id="definitions">Definitions</h4>

<ol>
<li>In this Act,</li>
</ol>

<dl>
<dt>“veteran”</dt>
<dd>means a person who has served in the Canadian Forces, either in combat or non-combat roles;</dd>

<dt>“domicile”</dt>
<dd>means an official registered residence of a citizen, specifically, but not limited to, a constructed home or empty plot of land;</dd>

<dt>“combat role”</dt>
<dd>is a role assigned to an individual who is faced with a task which is perceived to involve a confrontational nature;</dd>

<dt>“non-combat role”</dt>
<dd>is a role assigned to an individual who is faced with a task which is not perceived to involve a confrontational nature, but still may face danger due to their location and other factors.</dd>
</dl>

<h2 id="coming-into-force">Coming into Force</h2>

<h4 id="coming-into-force-1">Coming into force</h4>

<ol>
<li>This Act will come into force three months after it receives royal assent.  </li>
</ol>

<hr>

<p><strong>This Bill was submitted by /u/stvey with recommendation for Her Majesty’s Government.</strong></p></div></body>
